From 31320ccb09a06df35d1cd1fe2531c55fe983ca19 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilan Peer <ilan.peer@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 5 Feb 2025 11:39:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: cfg80211: Fix trace print for removed links
Git-commit: 31320ccb09a06df35d1cd1fe2531c55fe983ca19
Patch-mainline: v6.15-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14425

Print the mask of removed links in hexadecimal.

Signed-off-by: Ilan Peer <ilan.peer@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Johannes Berg <johannes.berg@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Miri Korenblit <miriam.rachel.korenblit@intel.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250205110958.1dd2831cab5f.Ib9f5e82286f0352cd057b4bf76737223e9de8274@changeid
Signed-off-by: Johannes Berg <johannes.berg@intel.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 net/wireless/trace.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/wireless/trace.h b/net/wireless/trace.h
index 4f0abd5d49df..9aa8081ca454 100644
--- a/net/wireless/trace.h
+++ b/net/wireless/trace.h
@@ -4118,7 +4118,7 @@ TRACE_EVENT(cfg80211_links_removed,
 		NETDEV_ASSIGN;
 		__entry->link_mask = link_mask;
 	),
-	TP_printk(NETDEV_PR_FMT ", link_mask:%u", NETDEV_PR_ARG,
+	TP_printk(NETDEV_PR_FMT ", link_mask:0x%x", NETDEV_PR_ARG,
 		  __entry->link_mask)
 );
 
-- 
